* Setup

** Python
https://www.python.org/download/releases/2.7/

If you know how to use ~virtualenv~, feel free to create a separate environment for this class.

*** Mac
On recent versions of Mac OS, simply use the built-in Python 2. Just run ~sudo easy_install pip~ and prefix all future ~pip~ commands with ~sudo~.

*** Windows
- 32-bit: https://www.python.org/ftp/python/2.7/python-2.7.msi
- 64-bit: https://www.python.org/ftp/python/2.7/python-2.7.amd64.msi

Please use PowerShell to do your work in this class.

Be sure to set up your system PATH:

#+BEGIN_SRC
[Environment]::SetEnvironmentVariable("Path", "$env:Path;C:\Python27;C:\Python27\Scripts", "User")
#+END_SRC

In order to install NumPy, you need to install the Microsoft Visual C++ compiler for Python 2.7: http://www.microsoft.com/en-us/download/confirmation.aspx?id=44266

** MySQL
https://dev.mysql.com/downloads/mysql/

*** Mac
- https://dev.mysql.com/downloads/file/?id=459872

*** Windows
- https://dev.mysql.com/downloads/file/?id=459896
To install an MSI, right-click it and select "Install".

** Atom (text editor)
https://atom.io

*** Mac
- https://github.com/atom/atom/releases/download/v1.0.19/atom-mac.zip

*** Windows
- https://github.com/atom/atom/releases/download/v1.0.19/AtomSetup.exe
- https://github.com/atom/atom/releases/download/v1.0.19/atom-windows.zip

*** Optional alternative text editor for Mac OS: TextWrangler
http://www.barebones.com/products/textwrangler/

*** Optional alternative text editor: Notepad++
http://notepad-plus-plus.org/
